item.dc:creator: @kilop kilop
item.description:
@kilop wrote:

Fishing spot is an npc, go into your config file and find npc.cfg. The IDs for them are

233, 234, 235, 236, 301, 302, 303, 304, 305, 306, 307, 308, 309, 310, 311, 312, 313, 314, 315, 316, 317, 318, 319, 320, 321, 322, 323, 324, 325, 326, 327, 328, 329, 330, 331, 332, 333, and 334. Use whichever ones you like.

item.dc:creator: @Axiom_Owner Axiom Owner
item.description:
@Axiom_Owner wrote:

[quote=“CoonHunter, post:5, topic:347079”][quote author=CookieScape link=topic=443457.msg3256277#msg3256277 date=1278126230]
The fence problem is with your global object, just find the object id of a fence and change your global object to that instead of the current one.
[/quote]
Typically this is not the case, because those are items. Please, use some logic. Items are not placed the same way as objects, nor do they block an object from showing when placed in that area. It is obviously a model problem, that the fence model was over-written with another.[/quote]
is there a tut on this or would you know?

item.title: 2 Questions?
item.dc:creator: @CoonHunter CoonHunter
item.description:
@CoonHunter wrote:

CookieScape:

The fence problem is with your global object, just find the object id of a fence and change your global object to that instead of the current one.

Typically this is not the case, because those are items. Please, use some logic. Items are not placed the same way as objects, nor do they block an object from showing when placed in that area. It is obviously a model problem, that the fence model was over-written with another.
